=============
Erlang Domain
=============

This is the Erlang domain for Sphinx 1.0.
Sphinx 1.0 will deliver new feature -- Domain.
It will enable other language support in addition to Python and C language.

This extension provides directives and roles to write Erlang documents.
Erlang Domain supports following directives:

* ``erl:module``
* ``erl:currentmodule``
* ``erl:function``
* ``erl:record``
* ``erl:macro``

And this domain supports following roles:

* ``:erl:mod:``
* ``:erl:func:``
* ``:erl:record:``
* ``:erl:macro:``

See doc/reference for detail.
